# Message Broker System

> Lightweight, developer-friendly message broker with Queue (Pointâ€‘toâ€‘Point) & Topic (Publishâ€‘Subscribe) patterns, built for Python services and easy noâ€‘code integrations (n8n, webhooks).

---

## âœ¨ Highlights / Features

* **Queue (Pointâ€‘toâ€‘Point)**: one message â†’ exactly one consumer (supports **competing consumers**)
* **Topic (Publishâ€‘Subscribe)**: one message â†’ multiple subscribers
* **Routing Keys & Wildcards**: `order.*`, `*.created`, `payment.#` (multi-level)
* **Acknowledgements**: manual/auto **ACK**, **NACK**, **requeue**
* **Observability**: `/health`, `/metrics`, basic queue stats
* **Auth**: API Key / Bearer Token; CORS configurable

> **Note**: This README is templateâ€‘ready. Update the **ENV**, **docker-compose**, and **Tech Stack** sections to match your setup exactly.

---

